**Plan:** Fix `%v` → `%w` in `fmt.Errorf` to properly wrap `ErrNotFound`.

The bug is on line 17: `fmt.Errorf("lookup %q: %v", id, ErrNotFound)` uses `%v` which stringifies the error instead of wrapping it. `%w` wraps it so `errors.Is` works.Both tests pass. The fix was changing `%v` to `%w` on **internal/fetch/fetch.go:17**:

```go
// Before (broken):
return "", fmt.Errorf("lookup %q: %v", id, ErrNotFound)
// After (fixed):
return "", fmt.Errorf("lookup %q: %w", id, ErrNotFound)
```

`%v` stringifies the error — it embeds the message but doesn't wrap, so `errors.Is` can't see through it. `%w` properly wraps the error, making `ErrNotFound` detectable by `errors.Is` while preserving the same error message text.
